Privacy Policy – Sir Roastington Bot

Last Updated: January 4, 2026

1. Information We Collect

Discord User Data: Only collects publicly available username, profile picture, and “About” information when interacting with bot commands.

Interaction Logs: Temporary in-memory storage for processing /decode or /sir commands; no permanent storage.

LLM Queries: Sent to Google Gemini API for text generation. Only prompts needed for functionality are transmitted.

2. How We Use Information

Generate roasts, explanations, and answers for Discord commands.

Maintain correct contextual responses (e.g., previous messages for /decode or mentions in /sir).

Never share, sell, or publicly display user data.

3. Data Retention

All Discord message data accessed is temporary; bot does not store any personal messages permanently.

Only short-term memory is used for generating context-aware responses in real-time.

4. Third-Party Services

Google Gemini API is used for LLM text generation. User input is sent to this API for processing only.

5. User Rights

You may disable or remove the bot from your server at any time.

Bot respects Discord’s privacy policies and community guidelines.

